  "notes": "The EA888 Gen 3b 2.0T is the evolution of the Gen 3 architecture, distinguished primarily by its longer 92.8mm stroke versus the 1.8T's 84.2mm, yielding 1984cc displacement. The block deck height is identical, making the two engines externally nearly indistinguishable. The Gen 3b introduces dual injection (combined direct injection + port injection, known as DISI or combined injection) on higher-output variants such as the Golf R (DNPA/DNWA codes) and later GTI (DKZA/CZPB codes), which significantly reduces intake valve carbon buildup — a known weakness of GDI-only engines including the Gen 3 1.8T. The IS20 turbocharger is used in GTI applications (220-228hp); the IS38 is used in Golf R and S3 applications (280-310hp). Compression ratio is 9.6:1 on most variants. The Gen 3b 2.0T is a direct mechanical upgrade into MQ7-platform vehicles equipped with the 1.8T Gen 3, requiring ECU swap and appropriate transaxle (DSG DQ381 recommended for higher-power builds). Aftermarket support is extensive; Stage 2 IS38 builds routinely achieve 340-370hp on pump gas.",
